He was now expected to take his Foreign Minister Ernest Bevin to the Potsdam Conference, for talks with Soviet leader Joseph Stalin and US President Harry Truman. 93 years ago (1929) The Geneva Convention was signed by 53 countries in an attempt to ensure the humane treatment of captured military and medical personnel and civilians during war. The agreement specified prisoners must be treated with compassion, and established the International Red Cross as the main neutral organisation responsible for assisting them. 19 years ago (2003) Comedy legend Bob Hope died two months after his 100th birthday. Born Leslie Townes Hope in London, he moved to America as a child. He was awarded an honorary knighthood by the Queen in 1998. 